comments: This was harder than I thought and I also have one paralyzed arm so it wasn't that easy.
at points, when the words were appearing, the words stopped making sense. similar to when you repeat a word so many times it begins to lose meaning and just sounds like gibberish. same concept.
Interesting and challenging at the same time. Nice day.

On the practice it seems to be a little odd since I felt like the name of the shape would be shown for a split second and switch to another shape.

For instance, Circle (for a millisecond) and then it would switch to Triangle and then the shape would appear. I don't know if that was intentional. Didn't see any other issues.

As far as vision, my vision is pretty good - but I do have split vision which I tend to squint to compensate for.

It seemed fatigue stared to affect my accuracy, especially during the 2nd portion of the experiment--with clues given, one would assume that accuracy would increase.  I'm not sure that was correct in my case.

Regardless, very interesting and fun study, thanks.
